Package: genproc
Title: Robust, Logged and Reproducible Iteration at Organizational Scale
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Daniel", "Rakotomalala", , "rakdanielh@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A framework that turns one-off iterative R procedures (such
    as 'for' loops, 'lapply()' or 'purrr::pmap()') into production-grade
    workflows by wrapping them with orthogonal, composable execution
    layers. Two layers are always active: structured logging with real
    traceback and per-case timing; and reproducibility capture, which
    records the R version, loaded package versions, execution environment,
    and the exact iteration mask. Parallel execution (via the 'future'
    ecosystem) and non-blocking background jobs are implemented as
    optional, composable layers. Further layers (monitored progress, error
    replay, input file hashing) are planned and will remain composable
    with the default layers.
